Node.Notes: Uncertain whether "his messengers" and "his servants" should be O or O2. Heb1:7 quotes LXX and both have "his messengers/angels" and "his servants" as O. Many believe in context of natural phenomenon in ps104, "winds" and "flaming fire" should be O instead.

Grammatical construction of vv 14b–15 is uncertain and has been variously explained. Tree assumes a pattern of external parallelism with a divine subject throughout, with infinivites of purpose twice continued with imperfect forms.
Assumes "cedars of Lebanon" from previous verse.
Assumes "roaring" from first half of verse.
